testimony: I wouldn’t say very much. I’m quite insecure and don’t like my own body, but I love other women’s bodies

I have clone sex fantasies. I have made art of sexual encounters between two representations of myself. It is only partially about being sexually attracted to myself/my body (although that is a factor). A lot of it is the fantasy of sex with someone who completely understands and shares my preferences. I am transitioning from female to neutral/androgynous so gender dysphoria colors my perception of femininity and I prefer not to think about myself as being feminine, having a female body etc.
I did not fantasize sexually about my body, like my breasts or voice, until I started consuming visual forms of pornography.

sexual_behavior: Cisgender Men, Non-Binary (Assigned Male at Birth)
testimony: I am uncomfortable with my body image so, alone, I usually fantasize out-of-body experiences. But with a partner, I feel most aroused when the experience brings me back to enjoyment of my own body, in addition to feeling aroused by my partner's body and my perception of their pleasure/enjoyment.

sexual_behavior: Cisgender Men, Cisgender Women, Non-Binary (Assigned Female at Birth)
testimony: I love the idea of my own body being turned on.

At 66, I've settled into celibacy.  Sex is something I do by myself, for myself.  It centres around my happiness with my body, which is something that's developed over the years.  I haven't always been happy with my body, but I've come to value it more and more as time has gone on.  Sex is a way for my body and mind to celebrate together.  :-)
I don't think much about myself when I'm horny. My thoughts are usually centered around other people.

I don’t feel like I’m turned on by my own body in any way so I found this survey confusing, didn’t know that was a thing. Seems kinda self absorbed but hey if it’s normal then who am I to judge, plus we don’t control what arouses us. Anyway most of my perception of my own body relates to how others would be viewing it not myself. If I think I look good, I’m mainly thinking about how I look good for my partner and my own insecurities.

sexual_behavior: Cisgender Men, Cisgender Women, Transgender Women, Non-Binary (Assigned Female at Birth)
testimony:
i have a need to feel attractive during sex, before i started transitioning sex very much felt like going through the motions, hyper focused on my form and my need to please, to be as good a partner as possible for my partner, thinking of an ugly face, an ugly moan leaking from my body would be enough for me to discard the entire sexual encounter because of my deep inherent need to know that i *look good*, a mistake in the facade would be devastating.  
i feel like my need to be submissive is easily just the continuation of that facade, instead of being purely sexual i choose to submit myself to the rigours of trying to pass, and its through this internal submission i find myself.
 my sexual fantasies used to be many, perhaps to fill the void, perhaps i was just more eager, 
now i'm on the correct sex hormones, i don't feel half as much shame during sex, i still get shy, embarrassed occasionally, i just also feel more willing to make mistakes during, its a more fun activity now, possibly exacerbated by my current partners being better.

sexual_behavior: Cisgender Men, Cisgender Women, Non-Binary (Assigned Female at Birth), Non-Binary (Assigned Male at Birth)
testimony: Feeling like you are sexy is a definite turn-on, just not one I experience very often. For me, "feeling sexy" isn't necessarily about looking a certain gendered way but about how good you look, whatever the category (i.e. hot guys and hot gals are both still hot lol).
If my body's gross then that's a turnoff. It kind of feels like having a "correct" body is...I'm not sure if I would say it's a prereq or if it's the foundation.

I want my body to be attractive to my partners, so I put a lot of effort into being attractive to other women. When I’m with someone who’s into me, I’m very satisfied that I’ve achieved that goal, but my body plays no role in my fantasies.
